"200B":{"department":"EDUC","number":"200B","title":"Introduction to Qualitative Research Methods","description":"(Formerly EDUC 151.) Primarily for master's students: An introduction to the core concepts and methods of qualitative research. Through a variety of hands-on learning activities, readings, field experiences, class lectures, and discussions, students will explore the processes and products of qualitative inquiry.nnThis is a graduate level course. No undergraduates may enroll. Priority will be given to GSE students, and final enrollment depends on instructor approval after the first day of class.","min_units":4,"max_units":4,"gers":[],"id":101489,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Pope, D."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,false,true,false],"start":"12:15:00 PM","end":"3:05:00 PM","instructors":["Pope, D."],"location":"Ceras 204"}],"id":12130}],[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Wolf, J."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,true,false,false,false],"start":"3:15:00 PM","end":"6:05:00 PM","instructors":["Wolf, J."],"location":"School of Education 334"}],"id":3210}],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
"200C":{"department":"EDUC","number":"200C","title":"Introduction to Statistical Methods in Education","description":"(Formerly EDUC 160.) Basic techniques in descriptive and inferential statistics for educational research will be covered with an emphasis on rigorous preparation for intermediate and advanced courses.  Topics include central tendency, variance, probability, distributions, confidence interval, t-test, F-test, correlation, regression, and analysis of variance. Non-parametric statistics and graphical principles for data representation will also be addressed.  Students will also be introduced to STATA in preparation for subsequent higher level courses.","min_units":3,"max_units":4,"gers":[],"id":101496,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Schwartz, D."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[true,false,true,false,true],"start":"1:15:00 PM","end":"2:20:00 PM","instructors":["Schwartz, D."],"location":"Ceras 300"}],"id":12254}],[],[]],"primary_type":"Lecture","secondary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Shear, B."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,true,false,false],"start":"2:30:00 PM","end":"3:20:00 PM","instructors":["Shear, B."],"location":"Ceras 108"}],"id":12356}],[],[]],"secondary_type":"Discussion"},
"202":{"department":"EDUC","number":"202","title":"Introduction to Comparative and International Education","description":"Contemporary theoretical debates about educational change and development, and the international dimension of issues in education. Emphasis is on the development of students' abilities to make cross-national and historical comparisons of educational phenomena.","min_units":4,"max_units":5,"gers":[],"id":101577,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Irving, M."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,true,false,true,false],"start":"2:15:00 PM","end":"4:05:00 PM","instructors":["Irving, M."],"location":"School of Education 206"}],"id":12083}],[],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
"202I":{"department":"EDUC","number":"202I","title":"International Education Policy Workshop","description":"This is a project-based workshop. Practical introduction to issues in educational policy making, education reform, educational planning, implementation of policy interventions, and monitoring and evaluation in developing country contexts. Preference to students enrolled in ICE/IEAPA, but open to other students interested in international development or comparative public policy with instructor's consent. Attendance at first class required for enrollment.","min_units":4,"max_units":4,"gers":[],"id":101578,"primary":[[],[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Kijima, R."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,false,true,false],"start":"1:15:00 PM","end":"3:05:00 PM","instructors":["Kijima, R."],"location":"90-92Q"}],"id":3402}],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
"203A":{"department":"EDUC","number":"203A","title":"Tutoring: Seeing a Child through Literacy (EDUC 103A)","description":"Experience tutoring grade school readers in a low income community near Stanford under supervision. Training in tutoring; the role of instruction in developing literacy; challenges facing low income students and those whose first language is not English. How to see school and print through the eyes of a child. Ravenswood Reads tutors encouraged to enroll. Service Learning Course (certified by Haas Center). May be repeated for credit.","min_units":3,"max_units":4,"gers":[],"id":215771,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Juel, C."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,true,false,false,false],"start":"7:15:00 PM","end":"9:05:00 PM","instructors":["Juel, C."],"location":"Ceras 204"}],"id":29369}],[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Juel, C."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,true,false,false,false],"start":"7:15:00 PM","end":"9:05:00 PM","instructors":["Juel, C."],"location":"Ceras 300"}],"id":29736}],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
