"220C":{"department":"EDUC","number":"220C","title":"Education and Society (EDUC 120C, SOC 130, SOC 230)","description":"The effects of schools and schooling on individuals, the stratification system, and society. Education as socializing individuals and as legitimizing social institutions. The social and individual factors affecting the expansion of schooling, individual educational attainment, and the organizational structure of schooling.","min_units":4,"max_units":5,"gers":[],"id":124478,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Ramirez, F."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[true,false,true,false,true],"start":"11:00:00 AM","end":"11:50:00 AM","instructors":["Ramirez, F."],"location":"School of Education 334"}],"id":12402}],[],[]],"primary_type":"Lecture"},
"220D":{"department":"EDUC","number":"220D","title":"History of School Reform: Origins, Policies, Outcomes, and Explanations (HISTORY 258E)","description":"Required for students in the POLS M.A. program; others welcome. Focus is on 20th-century U.S. Intended and unintended patterns in school change; the paradox of reform that schools are often reforming but never seem to change much; rhetorics of reform and factors that inhibit change. Case studies emphasize the American high school.nnThis course is required for POLS students pursuing the PreK-12 concentration.","min_units":3,"max_units":5,"gers":[],"id":101640,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Kelly, M."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[true,false,true,false,false],"start":"1:15:00 PM","end":"3:05:00 PM","instructors":["Kelly, M.","Labaree, D."],"location":""}],"id":29438}],[],[]],"primary_type":"Lecture","secondary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Kelly, M."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,true,false,false],"start":"3:15:00 PM","end":"4:05:00 PM","instructors":["Kelly, M."],"location":"School of Education 206"}],"id":29952},{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Kelly, M."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,true,false,false],"start":"2:00:00 PM","end":"3:05:00 PM","instructors":["Kelly, M."],"location":"School of Education 207"}],"id":29951}],[],[]],"secondary_type":"Discussion"},
"226X":{"department":"EDUC","number":"226X","title":"Curating Experience: Representation in and beyond Museums (AMSTUD 226X, CSRE 226X)","description":"In an age when some 50% of museum visitors only \"visit\" museums online and when digital technologies have broken open archival access, anyone can be a curator, a critic, an historian, an archivist. In this context, how do museums create experiences that teach visitors about who they are and about the world around them? What are the politics of representation that shape learning in these environments? Using an experimental instructional approach, students will reconsider and redefine what it means to curate experience.","min_units":2,"max_units":4,"gers":[],"id":214597,"primary":[[],[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Kelman, A."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,true,false,false],"start":"10:00:00 AM","end":"12:50:00 PM","instructors":["Kelman, A."],"location":"School of Education 210"}],"id":29693}],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
"227X":{"department":"EDUC","number":"227X","title":"Education Policy in the United States (for Master's Students)","description":"The course will provide students from different disciplines with an understanding of the broad educational policy context.  The course will cover topics including a) school finance systems; b) an overview of policies defining and shaping the sectors and institutional forms of schooling, c) an overview of school governance, d) educational human-resource policy, e) school accountability policies at the federal and state levels; and f) school assignment policies and law, including intra- and inter-district choice policies, desegregation law and policy. This course intended for Master's students.","min_units":3,"max_units":3,"gers":[],"id":215880,"primary":[[{"primary-instructors":[],"secondary-instructors":["Loeb, S."],"meeting-times":[{"days":[false,false,false,true,false],"start":"10:00:00 AM","end":"1:00:00 PM","instructors":["Loeb, S."],"location":"GSB Faculty East 101"}],"id":29724}],[],[]],"primary_type":"Seminar"},
